SIMPLE: long-winded
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Long-winded
<hw>Long"-wind"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Long-breathed; hence, tediously long in speaking; consuming much
time; <as>as, a <ex>long-winded</ex> talker</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A tedious, <qex>long-winded</qex> harangue.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>using or containing too many words; <as>as,
<ex>long-winded</ex> (or windy) speakers</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tedious, verbose, windy, wordy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Long"-wind"ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Longwise</ent>⟦br⟧
